HEADWORD: Pirogue
<hw>Pi*rogue"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Originally an
American Indian word: cf. F. <ets>pirogue</ets>, Sp. <ets>piroga</ets>,
<ets>piragua</ets>.]</ety> <def>A dugout canoe; by extension, any small
boat.</def> <altsp>[Written variously <asp>periauger</asp>,
<asp>perogue</asp>, <asp>piragua</asp>, <asp>periagua</asp>,
etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pirouette</ent>⟦br⟧
